Package: datatableEZ
Type: Package
Title: A convinient wrapper for DT package
Version: 0.0.1
Author: Vadim Bondarenko
Maintainer: Vadim Bondarenko <vadimus202@gmail.com>
URL: https://github.com/vadimus202/datatableEZ
BugReports: https://github.com/vadimus202/datatableEZ/issues
Description: The DT package is a wrapper of the JavaScript library 'DataTables', 
    and is a powerful way of rendering HTML tables from R dataframes using 
    JavaScript, usually via Markdown or Shiny. This package is mostly a wrapper 
    around DT::datatable() with more convenient defaults and simplified syntax.     
    The most common elements of the options() list argument are moved
    to direct arguments list datatable_EZ function. This avoids the need to
    include a long list of options (which is not fully documented in the 
    DT package documentation). See the vignette for most common usage examples.
License: GPL-3 | file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.3.2)
Imports: DT (>= 0.2),
    RColorBrewer,
    magrittr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
